---
import BrandbookLayout from '../../layouts/BrandbookLayout.astro';
import SectionLabel from '../../components/SectionLabel.astro';
import DosDonts from '../../components/DosDonts.astro';
---

<BrandbookLayout
  title="Brand Guidelines"
  pageName="BRAND GUIDELINES"
  description="Mission, vision, values, brand voice, tone, and personality for Reis IA."
>
  <!-- Title Area -->
  <section style="background: var(--surface-0);">
    <div class="container-standard" style="padding-top: var(--space-3xl); padding-bottom: var(--space-2xl);">
      <div class="max-w-[900px]">
        <h1
          class="font-bold tracking-tight mb-6"
          style="font-size: var(--text-display); line-height: 1.05; letter-spacing: -0.03em; color: var(--text-primary); text-wrap: balance;"
        >
          Brand Guidelines
        </h1>
        <p
          class="max-w-[680px]"
          style="font-size: var(--text-body-lg); line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text-secondary); text-wrap: pretty;"
        >
          The foundational rules that govern how Reis IA presents itself across every touchpoint.
          Every visual decision serves premium positioning, authority, and conversion.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="gradient-divider"></div>

  <!-- Section 01: Design Philosophy -->
  <section style="background: var(--surface-1);">
    <div class="container-standard" style="padding-top: var(--space-3xl); padding-bottom: var(--space-3xl);">
      <SectionLabel number="01" title="Design Philosophy" />

      <div class="max-w-[680px] space-y-8">
        <p style="font-size: var(--text-body-lg); color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.6; text-wrap: pretty;">
          Five principles govern every visual decision. They are ordered by priority — when two principles conflict, the higher-ranked one wins.
        </p>

        <!-- Principle Cards -->
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div
            class="p-6 rounded-xl border transition-colors duration-300 hover:border-[var(--border-visible)]"
            style="background: var(--surface-2); border-color: var(--border-default);"
          >
            <div class="flex items-baseline gap-3 mb-3">
              <span class="font-mono text-[11px] font-bold" style="color: var(--accent-blue);">01</span>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold" style="color: var(--text-primary);">Restraint Is the Design</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm" style="color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.65; text-wrap: pretty;">
              Every element must earn its space. If removing something does not reduce comprehension or conversion, remove it. Black space is not emptiness — it is the primary visual device that signals premium positioning.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div
            class="p-6 rounded-xl border transition-colors duration-300 hover:border-[var(--border-visible)]"
            style="background: var(--surface-2); border-color: var(--border-default);"
          >
            <div class="flex items-baseline gap-3 mb-3">
              <span class="font-mono text-[11px] font-bold" style="color: var(--accent-blue);">02</span>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold" style="color: var(--text-primary);">Typography Is Architecture</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm" style="color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.65; text-wrap: pretty;">
              The type system does 90% of the hierarchy work. Headlines are large, confident, and tightly tracked. Body text is generous and readable. The contrast between dense impact and open legibility creates the visual rhythm of every page.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div
            class="p-6 rounded-xl border transition-colors duration-300 hover:border-[var(--border-visible)]"
            style="background: var(--surface-2); border-color: var(--border-default);"
          >
            <div class="flex items-baseline gap-3 mb-3">
              <span class="font-mono text-[11px] font-bold" style="color: var(--accent-blue);">03</span>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold" style="color: var(--text-primary);">Dark Mode Mastery</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm" style="color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.65; text-wrap: pretty;">
              This is not "white on black." It is a layered surface system where depth is communicated through subtle background value shifts, semi-transparent borders, and restrained glow effects. Shadows are nearly invisible. Elevation comes from background lightness, not shadow darkness.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div
            class="p-6 rounded-xl border transition-colors duration-300 hover:border-[var(--border-visible)]"
            style="background: var(--surface-2); border-color: var(--border-default);"
          >
            <div class="flex items-baseline gap-3 mb-3">
              <span class="font-mono text-[11px] font-bold" style="color: var(--accent-blue);">04</span>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold" style="color: var(--text-primary);">Conversion Through Clarity</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm" style="color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.65; text-wrap: pretty;">
              CTAs must be immediately visible. Visual flow must guide the eye toward the next action. The blue accent exists primarily for conversion elements. Every page leads to /agendar or /aplicar. The design never lets a visitor wonder "what should I do next?"
            </p>
          </div>

          <div
            class="p-6 rounded-xl border transition-colors duration-300 hover:border-[var(--border-visible)]"
            style="background: var(--surface-2); border-color: var(--border-default);"
          >
            <div class="flex items-baseline gap-3 mb-3">
              <span class="font-mono text-[11px] font-bold" style="color: var(--accent-blue);">05</span>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold" style="color: var(--text-primary);">Engineered Precision</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm" style="color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.65; text-wrap: pretty;">
              Every value is intentional. No default ease. No arbitrary spacing. No round-number border-radii when optical tuning produces a better result. The design system is engineered like the AI systems we build for clients.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="gradient-divider"></div>

  <!-- Section 02: Brand Voice -->
  <section style="background: var(--surface-0);">
    <div class="container-standard" style="padding-top: var(--space-3xl); padding-bottom: var(--space-3xl);">
      <SectionLabel number="02" title="Brand Voice & Tone" />

      <div class="max-w-[680px] space-y-8">
        <p style="font-size: var(--text-body-lg); color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.6; text-wrap: pretty;">
          Reis IA communicates with the authority of a senior strategist and the clarity of a trusted advisor.
          The voice is direct, confident, and outcome-focused — never salesy or generic.
        </p>

        <!-- Voice Attributes Grid -->
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <div
            class="p-5 rounded-xl border"
            style="background: var(--surface-2); border-color: var(--border-default);"
          >
            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold mb-2" style="color: var(--text-primary);">Authoritative</h4>
            <p class="text-xs" style="color: var(--text-tertiary); line-height: 1.6;">
              Speaks from experience and proven methodology. Never tentative or speculative.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div
            class="p-5 rounded-xl border"
            style="background: var(--surface-2); border-color: var(--border-default);"
          >
            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold mb-2" style="color: var(--text-primary);">Direct</h4>
            <p class="text-xs" style="color: var(--text-tertiary); line-height: 1.6;">
              Gets to the point. Respects the reader's time. No filler words or corporate jargon.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div
            class="p-5 rounded-xl border"
            style="background: var(--surface-2); border-color: var(--border-default);"
          >
            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold mb-2" style="color: var(--text-primary);">Outcome-Focused</h4>
            <p class="text-xs" style="color: var(--text-tertiary); line-height: 1.6;">
              Every statement connects to a measurable result. Features are always framed through the lens of business impact.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div
            class="p-5 rounded-xl border"
            style="background: var(--surface-2); border-color: var(--border-default);"
          >
            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold mb-2" style="color: var(--text-primary);">Premium</h4>
            <p class="text-xs" style="color: var(--text-tertiary); line-height: 1.6;">
              Signals exclusivity through restraint. Fewer words, more weight. The writing mirrors the design — spacious and intentional.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="gradient-divider"></div>

  <!-- Section 03: Brand Personality -->
  <section style="background: var(--surface-1);">
    <div class="container-standard" style="padding-top: var(--space-3xl); padding-bottom: var(--space-3xl);">
      <SectionLabel number="03" title="Brand Personality" />

      <div class="max-w-[680px] space-y-8">
        <p style="font-size: var(--text-body-lg); color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.6; text-wrap: pretty;">
          Reis IA is a high-ticket AI consultancy, not a SaaS product. The brand personality reflects a senior advisor who commands premium fees because of proven results and systematic methodology.
        </p>

        <!-- Personality Spectrum -->
        <div class="space-y-4">
          {[
            { left: 'Playful', right: 'Serious', position: 85 },
            { left: 'Casual', right: 'Professional', position: 80 },
            { left: 'Approachable', right: 'Exclusive', position: 70 },
            { left: 'Technical', right: 'Strategic', position: 65 },
            { left: 'Verbose', right: 'Concise', position: 90 },
          ].map(item => (
            <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
              <span class="w-24 text-right text-xs font-mono" style="color: var(--text-quaternary);">
                {item.left}
              </span>
              <div class="flex-1 relative h-2 rounded-full" style="background: var(--surface-3);">
                <div
                  class="absolute top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 w-3 h-3 rounded-full"
                  style={`left: ${item.position}%; background: var(--accent-blue); box-shadow: 0 0 12px var(--blue-30);`}
                ></div>
              </div>
              <span class="w-24 text-xs font-mono" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
                {item.right}
              </span>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="gradient-divider"></div>

  <!-- Section 04: Brand Context -->
  <section style="background: var(--surface-0);">
    <div class="container-standard" style="padding-top: var(--space-3xl); padding-bottom: var(--space-3xl);">
      <SectionLabel number="04" title="Context & Positioning" />

      <div class="max-w-[680px] space-y-6">
        <p style="font-size: var(--text-body-lg); color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.6; text-wrap: pretty;">
          Reis IA is an ecosystem focused on implementing and monetizing Artificial Intelligence for businesses, led by Moroni Reis. The ecosystem spans four pillars:
        </p>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          {[
            { name: 'Builder', desc: 'Direct AI implementation for businesses' },
            { name: 'Systems', desc: 'Scalable AI systems and automation' },
            { name: 'Partners', desc: 'Strategic AI partnerships' },
            { name: 'Network', desc: 'Community and knowledge sharing' },
          ].map(pillar => (
            <div
              class="p-5 rounded-xl border-t-2"
              style="background: var(--surface-2); border-color: var(--accent-blue); border-top-color: var(--accent-blue);"
            >
              <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold mb-1" style="color: var(--text-primary);">{pillar.name}</h4>
              <p class="text-xs" style="color: var(--text-tertiary); line-height: 1.6;">{pillar.desc}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>

        <div
          class="p-6 rounded-xl border"
          style="background: var(--surface-2); border-color: var(--border-default);"
        >
          <div class="font-mono text-[11px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider mb-3" style="color: var(--accent-blue);">
            Key Rule
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm" style="color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.65;">
            Every visual element serves premium positioning, authority, and conversion toward booking calls. All CTAs lead to <code>/agendar</code> or <code>/aplicar</code>. There are no pricing tables, tier cards, or SaaS-style layouts.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="gradient-divider"></div>

  <!-- Section 05: Dos and Don'ts -->
  <section style="background: var(--surface-1);">
    <div class="container-standard" style="padding-top: var(--space-3xl); padding-bottom: var(--space-3xl);">
      <SectionLabel number="05" title="Brand Guidelines — Dos & Don'ts" />

      <div class="space-y-8 max-w-[900px]">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
          Color Usage
        </h3>
        <DosDonts items={[
          { type: 'do', text: 'Use blue accent for CTAs, brand icons, and emphasis moments. Max 2 blue elements per viewport.' },
          { type: 'do', text: 'Use text-secondary (70% white) for body copy. Full white (100%) is for headlines only.' },
          { type: 'do', text: 'Alternate sections between Surface-0 (#000) and Surface-1 (#0A0A0A).' },
          { type: 'dont', text: 'Use blue for body text, borders (except featured card top border), or background fills. Blue is earned, not scattered.' },
          { type: 'dont', text: 'Use hex grays (#A3A3A3, #737373) for text. Use the opacity scale instead for consistency across surface tiers.' },
          { type: 'dont', text: 'Use more than one surface tier jump between adjacent sections. Surface-0 to Surface-3 is too jarring.' },
        ]} />

        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-12" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
          Typography
        </h3>
        <DosDonts items={[
          { type: 'do', text: 'Use text-wrap: balance on headings. Use text-wrap: pretty on body paragraphs.' },
          { type: 'do', text: 'Cap body text width at 680px. Cap headline width at 900px.' },
          { type: 'do', text: 'Tighten letter-spacing as font size increases (Display: -0.03em, Body: 0).' },
          { type: 'dont', text: 'Use ALL CAPS except for Label tokens (badges, section labels). Headlines are sentence case.' },
          { type: 'dont', text: 'Allow body text to stretch across the full 1200px container. Wide text blocks destroy readability.' },
          { type: 'dont', text: 'Use positive letter-spacing on headings. Only Labels (+0.05em) and Micro (+0.02em) get positive tracking.' },
        ]} />

        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-12" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
          Motion
        </h3>
        <DosDonts items={[
          { type: 'do', text: 'Use the 5 defined easing curves. Every animation must use one of them.' },
          { type: 'do', text: 'Keep hover transitions at 200ms. Keep entrance animations at 800ms with 150ms stagger.' },
          { type: 'dont', text: 'Use default CSS ease, ease-in-out, or linear for interactive animations.' },
          { type: 'dont', text: 'Use bounce, spring, or elastic easing. Nothing overshoots. Reis IA motion is precise, not playful.' },
        ]} />

        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-12" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
          Brand Motifs
        </h3>
        <DosDonts items={[
          { type: 'do', text: 'Place the hourglass in sections about time, efficiency, urgency, and AI impact.' },
          { type: 'do', text: 'Use the hourglass as a 3-5% opacity watermark (200-300px) behind key sections.' },
          { type: 'dont', text: 'Use any other icon as a brand watermark. The hourglass is the sole brand mark.' },
          { type: 'dont', text: 'Animate the hourglass with rotation or flipping. It is a static, grounded symbol.' },
        ]} />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BrandbookLayout>
